/app/docs/tts.md:13:It works anywhere OpenClaw can send audio; Telegram gets a round voice-note bubble.
/app/docs/tts.md:318:- **Telegram**: Opus voice note (`opus_48000_64` from ElevenLabs, `opus` from OpenAI).
/app/docs/tts.md:326:  - Telegram `sendVoice` accepts OGG/MP3/M4A; use OpenAI/ElevenLabs if you need
/app/docs/tts.md:330:OpenAI/ElevenLabs formats are fixed; Telegram expects Opus for voice-note UX.
/app/docs/tts.md:391:result is Telegram-compatible, the tool includes `[[audio_as_voice]]` so
/app/docs/tts.md:392:Telegram sends a voice bubble.
